         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden, ¶ 2/7/67 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to inform you, that at a meeting of the trustees of the Royal Park held this day I have been directed to submit for the consideration of the...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.07.02<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Grant</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">P67/7923, unit 750, VPRS 44/P inward registered and unregistered correspondence, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">Add minutes from Royal Park minute book. Also annotation on letter: 'no decision in Sch. 67/35 [...] Lewis 16.7.67'.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For a copy of this letter see A345 Royal Park Zoological Society letter and minute book, p. 27, Mitchell Library, Sydney.</p>
               </note>Melbourne bot. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2/7/67</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to inform you, that at a meeting of the trustees of the Royal Park held this day I have been directed to submit for the consideration of the Board of Land &amp; Works the propriety to establish the following additional regulation for the protection and management of the Royal Park.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>"Persons shall not assemble in any part of the Royal Park for the purpose of hearing or giving lectures and adresses or for hearing and preaching sermons, or for the purpose of making or witnessing an exhibition or performance of any kind; and no part of the said park shall be used for gatherings of people unless by and with the consent of the trustees."<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>G. Sprigg to M, 26 June 1867<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #2F1EF9; ">No amendment to the rules was published in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-style: italic; color: #2F1EF9; ">Victoria Government Gazette<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #2F1EF9; ">until 21 October 1870, p. 1569. The set of rules promulgated there included '7. No meeting or assemblage of people of any kind, or for any purpose, will be allowed in the park without the special sanction of the trustees'.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #2F1EF9; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The previous regulations, published 13 February 1866, p. 381, did not include a similar rule.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am also directed to state, that the desirability for the establishment of a regulation in the foregoing sense has been urged on the trustees by a representation recently made by the Acclimation-Council.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #2F1EF9; ">G. Sprigg to M, 26 June 1867</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #2F1EF9; ">, in this edition as 67-06-26a</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #2F1EF9; ">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your very obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller, M.D.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hon. Secr. to the Trustees of the Royal Park</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable the President of the Board of Land &amp; Works.</p>
         </div>
